\subsection{The Erasure Type}


\[
\begin{prooftree}
\ups{\nar\Gamma} \wprov \wid A : \wid \rtype
\justifies
\nar\Gamma \nprov \wipe \wid A : \nar\rtype
\end{prooftree}
\qquad
\begin{prooftree}
\ups{\nar\Gamma} \wprov \wid M : \wid A
\justifies
\nar\Gamma \nprov \berase(\wid M) : \wipe \wid A
\end{prooftree}
\qquad
\begin{prooftree}
{\nar\Gamma} \nprov \nar M : \erase{\wid A}
\justifies
\nar\Gamma \nprov \bmake(\nar M) : \wipe \wid A
\end{prooftree}
\]
\[
\begin{prooftree}
\nar\Gamma \nprov \nar M : \wipe \wid A
\justifies
\nar\Gamma \nprov \buse(\nar M) : |\wid A|
\end{prooftree}
\]
Definitional equality works like this. If $\nar\Gamma \nprov \nar M : \wipe \wid A$, then
\[
 \nar M \equiv_\eta \bmake(\buse(\nar M))
\]
and in general
\[
\buse(\bmake(\nar M)) \equiv_\beta \nar M\]
\[
\buse(\berase(\wid M)) \equiv_\beta \erase{\wid  M}
\]
Semantics:
\[\begin{array}{rcl}
{(\wipe \wid A)}^* &=& {\wid A}^*\\
(\berase(\wid M))^* &=& {\wid M}^*\\
(\bmake(\nar M))^* &=& {\nar M}^*\\
(\buse(\nar M))^* &=& {\nar M}^*\\
\end{array}
\]


