\subsubsection{Adjunction}
Observe that
\[
\begin{prooftree}
\[
\justifies
y \div \erase{\wid A}, t \div 1 \nprov y : \erase{\wid A}
\]
\[
\[
\[
\justifies
y \div \erase{\wid A}, t :: \T \wprov t : \gg(x\div 1).0
\]
\justifies
y \div \erase{\wid A}, t :: \T \nprov \bunglue(t) : 0
\]
\justifies
y \div \erase{\wid A}, t :: \T \nprov \babort(\bunglue(t)) : \pp y {\wid A}
\]
\justifies
y \div \erase{\wid A}, t : \T \wprov \epair {y} {\babort(\bunglue(t))} : \wid A
\end{prooftree}
\]
So let's define $\key^t(y) = \epair {y} {\babort(\bunglue(t))}$ so that we have
\[
\begin{prooftree}
\justifies
y \div \erase{\wid A}, t : \T \wprov \key^t(y) : \wid A
\end{prooftree}
\]

Suppose we have
\[ x : \T \to \wid A \prov \wid M : \wid B\]
we can then construct
\[
\begin{prooftree}
\[
\justifies
 y \div  \erase{\wid A} \prov [\lambda t . \key^t(y)/x]\wid M : \wid B
\]
\justifies
 y :  \wid A \prov \isurd ( [\lambda t . \key^t(y)/x]\wid M): \surd \wid B
\end{prooftree}
\]

and conversely if we have a
\[ y :  \wid A \prov \wid N : \surd \wid B\]
then we can construct
\[
\begin{prooftree}
\[
\justifies
 x : \T \to \wid A, t : \T \prov [x\ t/y]\wid N : \surd \wid B
\]
\justifies
 x : \T \to \wid A \prov \esurd(t. [x\ t/y]\wid N) : \wid B
\end{prooftree}
\]

Let's try round trips. Let's first expand out
\[\wid M  :=  \esurd(t. [x\ t/y]\wid N)\]
\[\wid N  :=   \isurd ( [\lambda t . \key^t(y)/x]\wid M)\]
to
\[\wid M  :=  \epair{ |[x\ \langle\rangle/y]\wid N|.1}{|[x\ \langle\rangle/y]\wid N|.2}   \]
\[\wid N  :=   \bglue(\langle  [\lambda t . y/x]\erase{\wid M}, \{ [\lambda t . \epair{y}{\babort(\bunglue(t))}/x]\wid M\}\rangle, \langle\rangle) \]

Here's the round trip for $\wid M$:
\[\wid M  :=  \epair{ |[x\ \langle\rangle/y]\wid N|.1}{|[x\ \langle\rangle/y]\wid N|.2}   \]
\[=  \epair{ |[x\ \langle\rangle/y]\wid N|.1}{|[x\ \langle\rangle/y](\bglue(\langle  [\lambda t . y/x]\erase{\wid M}, \{ [\lambda t . \epair{y}{\babort(\bunglue(t))}/x]\wid M\}\rangle, \langle\rangle))|.2}   \]
\[=  \epair{ |[x\ \langle\rangle/y]\wid N|.1}{|(\bglue(\langle  [\lambda t . (x\ \langle\rangle)/x]\erase{\wid M}, \{ [\lambda t . \epair{x\ \langle\rangle}{\babort(\bunglue(t))}/x]\wid M\}\rangle, \langle\rangle))|.2}   \]
\[=  \epair{ |[x\ \langle\rangle/y]\wid N|.1}{(\langle  [\lambda t . (x\ \langle\rangle)/x]\erase{\wid M}, \{ [\lambda t . \epair{x\ \langle\rangle}{\babort(\bunglue(t))}/x]\wid M\}\rangle).2}   \]
\[=  \epair{ |[x\ \langle\rangle/y]\wid N|.1}{ \{ [\lambda t . \epair{x\ \langle\rangle}{\babort(\bunglue(t))}/x]\wid M\}}   \]
\[\equiv_{\eta}    [\lambda t . \epair{x\ \langle\rangle}{\babort(\bunglue(t))}/x]\wid M  \]
\[\equiv_{\eta}^0   [\lambda t . \epair{x\ \langle\rangle}{\{x\ t\}}/x]\wid M  \]
\[\equiv_{\beta}^{\pp{x\ t}{\wid A}}   [\lambda t . x\ t/x]\wid M  \]
\[\equiv_{\eta}^{\T \to \wid A}    [x/x]\wid M   \]

Here's the round trip for $\wid N$:
\[\wid N  :=   \bglue(\langle  [\lambda t . y/x]\erase{\wid M}, \{ [\lambda t . \epair{y}{\babort(\bunglue(t))}/x]\wid M\}\rangle, \langle\rangle) \]
\[ = \bglue(\langle  [\lambda t . y/x]\erase{\wid M}, \{ [\lambda t . \epair{y}{\babort(\bunglue(t))}/x](\epair{ |[x\ \langle\rangle/y]\wid N|.1}{|[x\ \langle\rangle/y]\wid N|.2})\}\rangle, \langle\rangle) \]
\[ = \bglue(\langle  [\lambda t . y/x]\erase{\wid M}, \{ (\epair{ |[y/y]\wid N|.1}{|[y/y]\wid N|.2})\}\rangle, \langle\rangle) \]
\[ = \bglue(\langle  [\lambda t . y/x]\erase{\wid M}, \{ \epair{ |\wid N|.1}{|\wid N|.2}\}\rangle, \langle\rangle) \]
\[ = \bglue(\langle  [\lambda t . y/x]\erase{\wid M},  {|\wid N|.2}\rangle, \langle\rangle) \]
\[ = \bglue(\langle  \erase{\wid N}.1,  {|\wid N|.2}\rangle, \langle\rangle) \]
\[ = \bglue(\erase{\wid N}, \langle\rangle) \]
\[ = \bglue(|\wid N|, \bunglue (\wid N)) \]
\[ = \wid N \]

